<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900822-0032</DOCNO><DOCID>900822-0032.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- MGM/UA Communications Co.:   Firm Received $50 Million   In Payments From Pathe</HL><DATE>08/22/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2</SO><CO>   PCC MGM</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)</IN><LP>   MGM/UA Communications Co. said it received checks totaling$50 million from Pathe Communications Corp., the latest in aseries of payments toward Pathe's $1.3 billion acquisition ofMGM/UA.   After MGM/UA receives payment on the checks, Pathe willhave paid $303 million cash toward the merger and will havegiven MGM/UA a $75 million security interest in three filmsslated by Pathe. Pathe must make another $50 million paymentSept. 20, according to terms of the merger agreement.</LP><TEXT>   The agreement calls for MGM/UA shareholders to receive atotal of $21.50 a share, including a $4-a-share paymentdistributed on July 20. Payment of the remaining $17.50 ashare and closing of the merger is set to occur on or beforeOct. 23.</TEXT></DOC>